The paper proposes a framework that combines an encoder and a generator to learn disentangled representations in an unsupervised way. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. The paper also mentions that the encoder learns interpretable, disentangled representations which encode descriptive properties, indicating that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses generative adversarial networks (GANs), which are commonly used in the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions experiments on several data sets, suggesting that it may also belong to the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
